GDPR for Dummies Part 1 - Consent
---------

This part of GDPR for Dummies will cover the topic of Consent. Which is covered by Articles 6, 7 and 8.

Consent is one of the primary improvements of the GDPR over the old DPD (aka the Data Protection Act), and is defined as:

    any freely given, specific, informed and unambiguous indication of the data subject's wishes by which he or she by statement or by a clear affirmative action, signifies agreement to the processing of personal data relating to him or her.
    (Article 4(11))


>> can't assume consent (ie pre ticked boxes) aka affirmative consent
>> Withdraw at any time (article 7 p3)
>> Childrens data parental consent
>> Penalties for breaking these rules on consent

